FBIS4-38395 "drsov104_f_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 27 May 1994 National Affairs Crimean Security Service Affirms Loyalty to Ukraine Crimean Security Service Affirms Loyalty to Ukraine LD2705104394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0830 GMT 27 May 94 LD2705104394 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] Sevastopol, 26 May -- The Crimean security service personnel have declared their support for the Ukrainian president's edict disbanding the service. They confirmed their subordination to the Ukrainian leadership and expressed their willingness for close cooperation with the leaders of Crimea "for the sake of solving vital problems in the region." The appeal by the personnel of the Ukrainian security service directorate in Crimea to the Crimean president and parliament was published in the Crimean press.
